'''autonomic nervous system''' 

# {{anatomy}} In [[human]]s and other [[vertebrate]]s, the part of the [[nervous system]] that regulates the involuntary activity of the [[heart]], [[intestine]]s and glands. These activities include [[digestion]], [[respiration]], [[perspiration]], [[metabolism]], and the modulation of [[blood pressure]].

